Hyperlinks:
HTML links are hyperlinks.
The link allows the user to redirect from one page to another.
the hyperlinks can be text or image.
<a> Tag is used for specifying the links in HTML.
<a> stands for anchor.

Example:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
			<title>C3</title>
	</head>
<body>
<h1>Class 2 Finished</h1>
<a href="C3_D2.html">Next Page</a>
<hr>
<a href="C3_D3.html"><img src="abc.jpg"/></a>


</body>
</html>

========================================= 
Hyperlinks  attributes.

Link = Unvisited Link
Visited= When link is Visited.
Hover= When the mouse cursor is placed on the link
Active= When the hyperlink is clicked, link becomes active.
